
[1]aruspice

   ARUS'PICE, n. Written also haruspice. [L. aruspex, or haruspex, a
   soothsayer, or diviner, who attempted to foretell events by consulting
   the entrails of beasts slain in sacrifice.]

   A priest, in ancient Rome, whose business was to inspect the entrails
   of victims, killed in sacrifice, and by them to foretell future events.
